By hovering over a shape, you will see arrows heading away from it.
To create a linking arrow between two shapes, hover over the first shape
and drag one of these arrows onto the second.

![picture of shape with arrows](https://www.diagrams.net/assets/img/blog/custom-properties-hover.png)



To label a shape or an arrow, simply select it and start typing.
You can move the text for an arrow by selecting the arrow
and dragging the orange dot.
